	<div class="container p-2">
		<p class="text-center fs-2 "><b>Kharif Crops</b></p>
			<p class="text-center fs-2 ">June-October</p>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-4">
				<div class="card paint-card">
					<div class="card-body text-center">
						<img src="img/rice.jpg" width="350px" height="300px">
						<p class="fw-bold fs-5">Rice</p>
						<p>Rice is the most important Kharif crop of India. It is grown in rain-fed areas with hot and humid climates. Rice requires a temperature of 16-20 °C during the growing season and 18-32 °C during ripening. It needs rainfall from 150-200 cm. Urea has been one of the most important chemical Fertilizers for the crops and has been one of the instrumental factors in the increase in food grain production of the country.
						</p>
					
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="col-md-4">
				<div class="card paint-card">
					<div class="card-body text-center">
						<img src="img/cotton.jpg" width="350px" height="300px">
						<p class="fw-bold fs-5">Cotton</p>
						<p>Cotton is a Kharif crop that requires approximately 8 months to cultivate. Black soil has excellent water retaining property which enables cotton to grow even in the regions which do not receive enough rainfall. Also the texture of black soil and high humus content favours cotton as well. Fertilizer for cotton:N-P-K 20-10-10 fertilizer is more suitable</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="col-md-4">
				<div class="card paint-card">
					<div class="card-body text-center">
						<img src="img/maize.jpg" width="350px" height="300px">
						<p class="fw-bold fs-5">Maize</p>
					 <p>Maize is one of the most versatile emerging crops having wider adaptability under varied agro-climatic conditions. Globally, maize is known as queen of cereals because it has the highest genetic yield potential among the cereals.Maize can be grown successfully in variety of soils ranging from loamy sand to clay loam.Therefore, the fields having provision of proper drainage should be selected for cultivation of maize.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

		
				</div>
			</div>

		
		
			<br>


		<p class="text-center fs-2 "><b>Rabi Crops</b></p>
		<p class="text-center fs-2 ">November - April</p>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-4">
				<div class="card paint-card">
					<div class="card-body text-center">
						<img src="img/wheat.jpg" width="350px" height="300px">
						<p class="fw-bold fs-5">Wheat</p>
						<p>Wheat is one of the oldest and most important of the cereal crops. Wheat is mainly a rabi (winter) season crop in India. Wheat is grown in a variety of soils of India. The fertilizer KCL provides both K and Cl. Both of these nutrients are needed for wheat health.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="col-md-4">
				<div class="card paint-card">
					<div class="card-body text-center">
						<img src="img/mustard.jpg" width="350px" height="300px">
						<p class="fw-bold fs-5">Mustard</p>
						<p>Mustard thrives well in dry and cool climate. Mustard crop requires the temperatures between 10°C to 25°C. Mustard is a spice known for its flavoring capabilities and therapeutic value. Mustard leaves are used as a salad or vegetable. It is also used for industrial purposes. Mustard seeds contain protein, oil, carbohydrates, and micronutrients. Fertilizers used for mustard are  irrigated crop apply 50% N and entire dose of P2O5 and K2O as basal and rest 50% N at 3 weeks stage.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="col-md-4">
				<div class="card paint-card">
					<div class="card-body text-center">
						<img src="img/sunflower.jpg" width="350px" height="300px">
						<p class="fw-bold fs-5">SunFlower</p>
						<p>Sunflower, the name "Helianthus" is derived from ‘Helios’ meaning ‘sun’ and ‘anthus’ meaning ‘flower’. It is important oilseed crop of country. Sunflower oil is most popular because of its light color, bland flavour, high smoke point and high level of linoleic acid which is good for heart patient. It can be grown on wide range of soil from sandy loam to black soils. It gives best result when grown under fertile, well-drained soil. Fertilizer requirement (kg/acre)UREA:50 SSP:75 and MURIATE OF POTASH</p>
				</div>
			</div>
</div>
		</div>
