	<p class="text-center fs-2 "><b>Zaid Crops Crops</b></p>
		<p class="text-center fs-2 ">March - June</p>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-4">
				<div class="card paint-card">
					<div class="card-body text-center">
						<img src="img/sugar.jpg" width="350px" height="300px">
						<p class="fw-bold fs-5">SugarCane</p>
						<p>Sugarcane plant is a tuft of between 5 and 20 upright stems, or "tillers", 2m to 5m tall and 2cm to 4cm in diameter.It needs hot and humid climate with an average temperature of 21°C to 27°C. 75-150 cm rainfall is favorable for sugar cane cultivation. Irrigation needed for areas with lesser rainfall. </p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="col-md-4">
				<div class="card paint-card">
					<div class="card-body text-center">
						<img src="img/Bitter.jpg" width="350px" height="300px">
						<p class="fw-bold fs-5">BitterGuard</p>
						
						<p>Bitter gourd is an important vegetable crop and is grown for its immature tuberculate fruits which have a unique bitter taste. It is a warm season crop grown mainly in sub-tropical and hot-arid regions. Temperature range of 24o- 27oC is considered as optimum for the growth of the vines. Generally well decomposed FYM (15-20 t/ha) is mixed with the soil during ploughing. The recommended dose of fertilizer to be applied per hectare is 50-100 kg N, 40-60 kg P2O5 and 30-60 kg 25 K2O.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="col-md-4">
				<div class="card paint-card">
					<div class="card-body text-center">
						<img src="img/ground.jpg" width="350px" height="300px">
						<p class="fw-bold fs-5">Ground nut</p>
						<p>Groundnut is a leguminous crop which belong to the Leguminosae family. Groundnut plays an important role both as oil or food crop. Groundnut is very nutritious food. It contains 48-50 % oil, 26-28 % protein and a rich source of dietary fiber, minerals and vitamins. It is cultivated on large scale in well-drained sandy loam soil or sandy clay loam soil in India. Among the available nitrogenous fertilizers, ammonium sulphate is preferred for groundnut crop because of its sulphur content (24%).</p>
				</div>
			</div>
</div>
